OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1775913059
OL,3,CGreens win by-election to replace
OL,4,Cjailed Reform councillor
OL,6,FVoters went to the polls yesterday and
OL,7,Felected the Green's Rob Yates with
OL,8,F2,068 votes, a 39% share of the vote.
OL,10,FReform UK's Marc Rattigan came second
OL,11,Fwith 33%.
OL,13,FOf his victory, Mr Yates said: "This
OL,14,Fresult shows that across Kent and
OL,15,Facross the country the Greens are the
OL,16,Fantidote to Reform."
OL,18,FThe 39-year-old is an offshore wind
OL,19,Ffarmer and is currently a Thanet
OL,20,FDistrict Council member.
