OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1775913059
OL,3,CGreens win by-election to replace
OL,4,Cjailed Reform councillor
OL,6,FReform won control of Kent County
OL,7,FCouncil (KCC) in May last year,
OL,8,Fsecuring 57 out of 81 seats, but is
OL,9,Fcurrently down to 47 after removing
OL,10,Fsome of them.
OL,12,FLiberal Democrats make up 12 members,
OL,13,Fnewly-established Restore Britain Kent
OL,14,Fgroup make up seven, Conservatives
OL,15,Fhold six seats, Greens now hold six
OL,16,Ffollowing Mr Yates's win and Labour
OL,17,Fhave two.
